            "title": "Product Purity & Ingredients"
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-1": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What makes Badri Cow Ghee different from normal cow ghee?",
            "content": "Badri cows are native Himalayan humped cattle that free-graze on mountain medicinal herbs, fresh air, and organic plants in Uttarakhand. They produce a very limited quantity of A2 milk which is exceptionally rich in nutritional values, creating a deep golden, granular, and aromatic ghee."
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-2": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the traditional Bilona churning process?",
            "content": "The Bilona method is our traditional 5-step process. First, A2 milk is boiled slowly on earthen stoves using firewood. Second, the milk is cultured overnight in earthen pots. Third, the curd is churned back-and-forth slowly using wooden whisks to extract butter. Fourth, the butter is slowly melted on wood fires until water evaporates, leaving golden granular ghee."
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-3": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does Ghar Aangan Ghee contain lactose or casein?",
            "content": "During the slow simmering process of making ghee, the milk solids, lactose, and casein are completely separated and filtered out. As a result, Ghar Aangan ghee is virtually lactose-free and casein-free, making it easy to digest and suitable for most dairy-sensitive individuals."
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-4": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Why is the texture of the ghee granular (danedaar)?",
            "content": "A granular (danedaar) texture is a natural characteristic of high-quality, wood-fired Bilona ghee. When pure ghee is cooled slowly at room temperature, it crystallizes naturally. This granularity is proof of purity and authentic wooden churning."
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-title-2": {
          "type": "title",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Shipping & Delivery"
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-5": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How long does delivery take?",
            "content": "We dispatch all orders within 24-48 hours. Delivery usually takes 3 to 5 business days across India, depending on your location. You will receive a tracking link via email and WhatsApp as soon as your package is shipped."
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-6": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What packaging do you use for shipping?",
            "content": "We care about product integrity and the environment. Our ghee is packaged in premium glass jars and shipped in high-density, shock-absorbent eco-friendly boxes to ensure it arrives at your doorstep in perfect condition."
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-7": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do you offer free shipping?",
            "content": "Yes! We offer free shipping on all orders over ₹499 across India. For orders below this amount, a standard shipping fee of ₹49 is applied at checkout."
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-8": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do you ship internationally?",
            "content": "Currently, we ship only within India. However, we are working on expanding our logistics to bring the essence of Himalayan purity to customers globally soon. Stay tuned!"
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-title-3": {
          "type": "title",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Storage & Shelf Life"
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-9": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the shelf life of Ghar Aangan Ghee?",
            "content": "Pure wood-fired Bilona ghee is highly stable and has a long shelf life of 12-18 months at room temperature. Always store it in a cool, dry place and use a clean, dry spoon to prevent moisture from entering."
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-a": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Should I refrigerate the ghee?",
            "content": "No, pure ghee should never be refrigerated. Storing it in the refrigerator will introduce moisture and ruin its beautiful granular texture. Keep it in your kitchen pantry away from direct sunlight."
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-b": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Why does the color or aroma vary slightly between jars?",
            "content": "Our ghee is natural and handmade in small batches. Variations in color (from light yellow to deep gold) and aroma occur naturally depending on the seasonal pasture diet of our free-grazing Badri cows. This variation is a sign of an authentic, non-industrialized food product."
          }
        },
        "template--20718015545618__08421e50-b348-46a3-bbb7-5b26be196b6c-accordion_item-c": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can this ghee be used for high-heat cooking?",
            "content": "Absolutely. Pure A2 ghee has a very high smoke point of 250°C (482°F). Unlike unstable oils, it does not break down or release harmful free radicals at high temperatures, making it the healthiest choice for cooking, sautéing, and baking."
          }
        },
